NORTH AMERICAN ORGANISATION



The following announcement was made today by David Dey, Managing Director,
Communications Systems Division, in London via a videoconference link to the New
York Office:

"On the successful completion of his assignment to British Telecom Inc, Mike
Ford is returning to the United Kingdom on 30 April to take up an appointment as
Director Special Projects, reporting to David Dey. Mike will be involved in the
development of the new organisation through Project Sovereign. He will also
retain line management responsibility for CTG Canada and remain on the Board of
Mitel. As a result of Mike's move, the following appointment is announced.

Mark Baker is appointed President, British Telecom Inc, effective 1 May 1990, in
addition to his responsibilities as President and CEO of BT Tymnet."

In his remards to the company's senior managers who were present, David Dey
stressed that British Telecom Inc will continue as a business unit and will
grow, and he emphasised the strategic importance of a strong BT presence in New
York. He also stressed that the change in President did not mean that BT Inc was
to be folded into Tymnet. 

During the course of the year, plans will be developed to bring together BT
Tymnet and BT Inc into a single British Telecom trading company in USA under
Mark Baker, with the aim of providing the best possible interface with our US
customers for all BT services and products. This new company has the working
title of "British Telecom USA Inc". This coming together would run parallel to
the organisational changes in the UK. In the meantime, joint teams will be
established to ensure coordination of particular activities, eg Human Resources
and Treasury activities, where this is already in effect.

He also stated that a new Executive Vice President, British Telecom Inc will be
appointed very shortly, based in New York, to manage the day to day activities
of the company, reporting to Mark Baker. All those currently reporting to Mike
Ford  will report to the EVP.
